\newlabel{fig:paradigm_timeline}{{21}{69}{Structural parallels between CPU and LLM system evolution. Curved arrows connect milestones that share the same architectural driver: Dennard scaling collapse and the inference energy wall both arise from a \emph {Power Wall}; the multi-core and MoE transitions reflect a \emph {Parallelism Shift}; big.LITTLE and heterogeneous model orchestration embody \emph {Heterogeneity}; x86 ISA and the token/tool interface represent \emph {ISA Abstraction}; and domain accelerators and specialized small models pursue \emph {Specialization}}{figure.caption.120}{}}
